reason.tex:
%text
 Given two events $A$ and $B$, the following figures show what $A\cap B, A\cap B'$ and $A'\cap B$ look like
%
\begin{align}

\includegraphics[scale=1.4]{98-A.svg}
\end{align}
%text
 And one can see that if the three areas \underline\text{are added together} then one will get $A\cup B$. Which is why
\[\prob{A\cup B} = \prob{A\cap B} + \prob{A\cap B'} + \prob{A'\cap B} \]
%
